OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F434A1773936669
OL,3,CBusinesses sign letter after plans to
OL,4,Cwithdraw funding from night-time
OL,5,Ceconomy
OL,7,FMore than 100 businesses from
OL,8,FBristol's night-time economy have told
OL,9,Fthe city council they're concerned
OL,10,Fabout the future of a project
OL,11,Fhighlighting the city's nightlife.
OL,13,FThere are plans to close down Bristol
OL,14,FNights, a service which supports those
OL,15,Fwho work from 6pm to 6am.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/11
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,435,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43402
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F434A1773936669
OL,3,CBusinesses sign letter after plans to
OL,4,Cwithdraw funding from night-time
OL,5,Ceconomy
OL,7,FBristol City Council also aims to
OL,8,Fscrap the role of Bristol's Night Time
OL,9,FEconomy Advisor (NTEA), a position
OL,10,Fwhich has supported campaigns against
OL,11,Fthe spiking of drinks, protecting the
OL,12,Fsafety of women and girls, and improve
OL,13,Fbehaviour.
OL,15,FIn a letter, businesses say they are
OL,16,Fconcerned and shocked at proposals to
OL,17,Fdisband the partnership with Bristol
OL,18,FNights.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/11
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,435,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F434A1773936669
OL,3,CBusinesses sign letter after plans to
OL,4,Cwithdraw funding from night-time
OL,5,Ceconomy
OL,7,FHarrison Baillie is a member of staff
OL,8,Fat popular Bristol nightclub Thekla
OL,9,Fand also signed the letter.
OL,11,FHe said: "It's very concerning to us
OL,12,Fto see that Bristol Nights might be
OL,13,Fclosing and that we might be losing
OL,14,Fthe Night Time Economy Advisor.
OL,16,F"Having that direct line of
OL,17,Fcommunication with the council through
OL,18,Fthe NTEA, it's something we look very
OL,19,Fstrongly for to voice our concerns as
OL,20,Fvenues, and as a sector across the
OL,21,Findustry.
OL,26,@sD@JOUxD@AOU
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/11
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,435,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F434A1773936669
OL,3,CBusinesses sign letter after plans to
OL,4,Cwithdraw funding from night-time
OL,5,Ceconomy
OL,7,F"Back in 2017, we were some of the
OL,8,Fpeople at the forefront to call for
OL,9,Fthat position to be appointed so that
OL,10,Fwe could keep other venues afloat when
OL,11,Fwe're dealing with the Redcliffe Wharf
OL,12,Fdevelopment.
OL,14,F"So if we lose that point of access,
OL,15,Fit's very concerning to us as a venue."
OL,17,FAnnual spending in Bristol's bars,
OL,18,Frestaurants, theatres, and clubs
OL,19,Fgenerates more than #200 million a
OL,20,Fyear.
OL,26,@oD@AOUvD@AOUwD@gO]
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/11
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,435,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43405
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F434A1773936669
OL,3,CBusinesses sign letter after plans to
OL,4,Cwithdraw funding from night-time
OL,5,Ceconomy
OL,7,FIt employs around 116,000 which is
OL,8,Faround 41% of the city's entire
OL,9,Fworkforce.
OL,11,FClare Reddington is the CEO of
OL,12,FWatershed and said people in the
OL,13,Fsector are nervous about the move.
OL,15,FShe said: "Some people might not know
OL,16,Fthat Watershed and other cultural
OL,17,Fvenues are part of the night-time
OL,18,Feconomy along with bars, nightclubs,
OL,19,Fand venues.
OL,26,@wD@KOU
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/11
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,435,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43406
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F434A1773936669
OL,3,CBusinesses sign letter after plans to
OL,4,Cwithdraw funding from night-time
OL,5,Ceconomy
OL,7,F"They're places where people gather,
OL,8,Fthey get together, they bring joy, but
OL,9,Fyou've heard it's a really tough time
OL,10,Fso the sector needs to come together
OL,11,Fto have a joint approach and that's
OL,12,Fwhat Bristol Nights did so brilliantly.
OL,14,F"Bristol Nights was a partnership
OL,15,Fproject - that's what was so great
OL,16,Fabout it and that's why it's really
OL,17,Fgood value for money so I think we're
OL,18,Fhoping that (because of) everyone who
OL,19,Fsigned the letter, that the council
OL,20,Fwill sit down and we can think about
OL,21,Fwhat's next."
OL,26,@oD@AOUvD@AOUzD@MpmzD@Xpn}D@MO]
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/11
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
